# Line endings: normalize all text to LF on checkout.
#
# Git-for-Windows defaults to core.autocrlf=true, which rewrites tracked text files to CRLF
# on a Windows clone. That gives demo_tree.json and the *.sh entry points CRLF endings that
# diverge from the committed (LF) blobs and can break Git Bash scripts. Pinning eol=lf keeps
# the working tree byte-identical to what was committed and keeps the shell scripts runnable.
#
# NOTE: this does NOT fix the runtime bug where native-Windows Python writes CRLF on stdout
# (that is handled by stripping CR in start_demo.sh / scripts/resolve_python.sh). It fixes the
# separate file-on-disk problem, so `diagnose_demo_tree.sh` no longer reports working != committed.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets — never apply text/eol conversion.
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.ico   binary
*.pdf   binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
